claim.claim-text:
9. A method of constructing and using a data structure of images from a small specimen on a microscope slide comprising:
digitally scanning a first segment of the specimen and a second segment of the specimen, and acquiring digital image data of the first segment and the second segment useable to provide an overall magnified image of the specimen and higher optical magnification images of selected points on the specimen;
positioning the microscope slide with respect to a microscope lens at a first location where the first segment is scanned;
moving the microscope slide with respect to a microscope lens from the first location to a second location where the second segment is scanned, the second segment being abutted without any substantial overlap with the first segment so that the first segment and the second segment may be brought into contiguity without blurriness at the edges of the first segment and the second segment;
storing the scanned digital image data in a data structure of the image of the first segment and the image of the second segment;
transferring at least a portion of the data structure over an internet or intranet communication channel;
providing a control program configured to construct and display the overall magnified image from the image of the first segment and the image of the second segment;
receiving a selection input of a point on the overall magnified image; and
the control program being configured to retrieve the image of the first segment and the image of the second segment from the data structure and display a corresponding higher magnification image of the selected point.

24. A method of constructing and using a virtual microscope data structure of images from a specimen on a microscope slide comprising:
digitally scanning a first segment of the specimen on the microscope slide through a microscope lens and a second segment of the specimen on the microscope slide through the microscope lens, and acquiring scanned digital image data, the scanned digital image data being useable to create an overall magnified image of the specimen or a portion thereof and being useable to create a higher magnification image of a point on the specimen, the higher magnification image being at a higher magnification than the magnification of the overall image;
positioning the microscope slide with respect to the microscope lens at a first location where the first segment is scanned;
moving the microscope slide with respect to a microscope lens from the first location to a second location where the second segment is scanned, the second segment being abutted without any substantial overlap with the first segment so that the first segment and the second segment may be brought into contiguity without blurriness at the edges of the first segment and the second segment;
storing the scanned digital image data in a data structure of the image of the first segment and the image of the second segment;
transferring the scanned digital image data over an internet or intranet communication channel; and
providing a control program to retrieve the image of the first segment and the image of the second segment from the data structure and construct the overall magnified image of the specimen and a higher magnification image, the control program providing a simultaneous view of the overall magnified image and the higher magnification image.
